  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">This paper is concerned with the construction of a fast algorithm for computing the maximum speed of propagation in the Riemann solution for the Euler system of gas dynamics with the co-volume equation of state. The novelty in the algorithm is that it stops when a guaranteed upper bound for the maximum speed is reached with a prescribed accuracy. The convergence rate of the algorithm is cubic and the bound is guaranteed for gasses with the co-volume equation of state and the heat capacity ratio γ in the range <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>5</mn><mo stretchy="false">/</mo><mn>3</mn><mo stretchy="false">]</mo></math> .</subfield>
    <subfield code="9">Elsevier</subfield>
  </datafield>
